#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Cyclops_Ritualist, race=eoma_cyclops
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Barbarians\Cyclops_Ritualist.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Cyclops Ritualists are an exceptional subset of cyclopes known for their "
"proficiency in magical arts and intellect. They are the second-most "
"intelligent group within their species, after Lorekeepers. While the "
"majority of cyclopes remain unremarkable and lack intellectual prowess, "
"there are notable exceptions, especially among the noble bloodlines - "
"individuals with remarkable cognitive abilities even by human standards. "
"These gifted few undergo a rigorous initiation process to join the "
"prestigious ranks of Ritualists, serving as trusted assistants to the "
"revered Lorekeepers.\n"
"\n"
"The initiation process is part of a larger cyclops tradition, where the "
"nobles make a pilgrimage to the Lorekeepers' temples at least once in their "
"lives. Besides religious rituals, each cyclops noble attempts comprehensive "
"mental challenges set forth by Lorekeepers in their sacred temples. These "
"intricate puzzles test the aspirant's problem-solving acumen, memory, and "
"critical thinking skills. \n"
"\n"
"Most cyclopes fail the Lorekeepers' test, and many end up trying their luck "
"with the Barbarian army instead, but those who prove themselves worthy "
"through their intelligence and determination are granted entry into the "
"exclusive order of Ritualists. This honor is regarded as one of the greatest "
"accomplishments one can get in cyclops society. A sizeable percentage of the "
"Ritualists are also the Lorekeepers' own sons, taught from a young age to be "
"capable of passing the test.\n"
"\n"
"As Ritualists, these distinguished cyclopes work closely alongside "
"Lorekeepers, assisting them with various duties in the temples, learning the "
"intricacies of arcane magic, studying ancient history, and training to "
"someday become the next generation of Lorekeepers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Raging_Cyclops, race=eoma_cyclops
