#. [advancement]: id=shadowmage_knives
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Shadow_Mage.cfg:117
msgid "+1 damage and very skilled on cursed knives, +3 HP, +20% max XP"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Shadowmage, race=human
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Shadow_Mage.cfg:151
msgid ""
"The Shadowmagi are a subsection of the black mage group, who act as the Sky "
"Kingdom's spies. They wear special enchanted suits, which make their wearers "
"nearly impossible to see during night-time, but don't work as well in "
"daylight. Their job consists of observing other nations from the shadows, "
"sending the gathered intel to the Sky Kingdom via messages attached to "
"magical eyes every few months or so. They are also quite capable at "
"assassination, though the need for such drastic measures is extremely rare."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Shadow_Mage.cfg:246
msgid "cursed knives"
msgstr "诅咒小刀"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Sky_Guardian, race=human
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Sky_Guardian.cfg:4
msgid "Sky Guardian"
msgstr "天空守卫"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Sky_Guardian, race=human
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Sky_Guardian.cfg:36
msgid ""
"Sky Guardians are the Sky Kingdom's most elite troops. They usually act as "
"bodyguards of important members of the Sky Kingdom society (such the Guru "
"and high-ranking members of the Council of Masters), but are also sent on "
"the rare expeditions where extreme military presence is required. Their "
"weapon of choice is an unusual one: a long handle with a spear tip on one "
"end, and a mace head on the other. Normally such a weapon would be very "
"impractical, so it has been enchanted to dynamically redistribute the weight "
"according to the guardian's needs."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=blade
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Sky_Guardian.cfg:66
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Tharis\Dark_Executioner.cfg:28
msgid "blade"
msgstr "剑刃"

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Sky_Guardian.cfg:90
msgid "pike"
msgstr "叉"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Sorcerer, race=human
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Sorcerer.cfg:4
msgid "Sorcerer"
msgstr "术士"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Sorcerer, race=human
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Sorcerer.cfg:20
msgid ""
"While most battle magi are mediocre spellcasters, many, at some point in "
"their life, decide to fully dedicate themselves to learning advanced magic, "
"instead of just combat spells. These sorcerers spend most of their time in "
"the libraries, universities and philosopher meeting, they still pack quite a "
"punch with their attack spells, although their lack of daily physical "
"exercise weakened their skill with melee weapons. Some sorcerers, given "
"enough talent, even rise to the ranks of Master Magi..."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Subversive_Mage, race=human
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Subversive_Mage.cfg:4
msgid "Subversive Mage"
msgstr "叛逆法师"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Subversive_Mage, race=human
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Subversive_Mage.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Subversive Magi are an unusual group that studies black magic. They are "
"still novices, but they are good at evading enemy strikes, capable of "
"entangling enemies in nets made out of energy, and then battering them with "
"cold missiles."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Terramancer, race=human, description={NO_DESCR_AVAILABLE}
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Terramancer.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Aeromancer"
msgid "Terramancer"
msgstr "御气师"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Titan_Golem, race=mechanical, description={NO_DESCR_AVAILABLE}
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Titan_Golem.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "War Golem"
msgid "Titan Golem"
msgstr "战争傀儡"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Um, race=monster
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Um.cfg:4
msgid "Um"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Um, race=monster
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Um.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Ums ('um' in single) are the Sky Kingdom's top secret weapon. They represent "
"the pinnacle of Sky Kingdom's biological enhancement technology. Their "
"creation is a result of long, hard studies and experiments, requiring many "
"factors, including a fit Mu specimen, genetic modification, and extreme "
"amounts of nutrition. Their name means 'mind' in the language of one of the "
"nations the Sky Kingdom have observed. The power of the Ums is beyond that "
"of any other artificial being the Sky Kingdom has created."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=secret
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Um.cfg:112
msgid "um blast"
msgstr "爆破"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Void_Mage, race=human
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Void_Mage.cfg:4
msgid "Void Mage"
msgstr "虚空法师"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Void_Mage, race=human
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\Void_Mage.cfg:21
msgid ""
"While few Black Magi master their art, those who do are known as Void Magi. "
"Their skills are rivalled only by the Great Warlocks of Tharis."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Golem_Boss, race=mechanical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\War_Golem.cfg:4
msgid "War Golem"
msgstr "战争傀儡"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Golem_Boss, race=mechanical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\War_Golem.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Unlike the regular golems, war golems are made entirely from metal. They "
"also have a magic energy conducting device inside them, which can shoot "
"magic missiles at their foes. They are usually tasked with guarding "
"important locations, but are also sent on dangerous expeditions."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_War_Mage, race=human
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\War_Mage.cfg:4
msgid "War Mage"
msgstr "战法师"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_War_Mage, race=human
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Sky_Kingdom\War_Mage.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Though the Sky Kingdom's military is known to be fairly small, what it lacks "
"in quantity, it makes up in quality fairly well. The War Magi are versatile "
"troops, being quite good at both melee and ranged combat. They are generally "
"reserved for when military presence is really needed, similarly to the Sky "
"Guardians."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Air_Avatar, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Air_Avatar.cfg:4
msgid "Air Avatar"
msgstr "大气化身"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Air_Avatar, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Air_Avatar.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Air avatars have distinguished themselves from mere elementals, developing "
"into stormy vortexes, wind and dark clouds circulating inside and outside "
"itself. Avatars have transformed into breathing tempests. Gaining a more "
"substantial body, avatars are less susceptible the common weaponry of swords "
"and arrows. Air avatars guide themselves with the currents they have "
"created, drifting from place to place, crackling with lightning from within "
"their ethereal innards."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Air_Avatar.cfg:99
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Air_Elemental.cfg:67
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Air_God.cfg:98
msgid "hurricane"
msgstr "台风"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Air_Elemental, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Air_Elemental.cfg:4
msgid "Air Elemental"
msgstr "气元素"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Air_Elemental, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Air_Elemental.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Air elementals are magical entities built entirely out of the Abyssal "
"atmosphere. Summoned elementals, introduced in a world where air is "
"omnipresent, regenerate their bodies continually with time’s passage. Given "
"their anatomies, elementals of this variety are quick and evasive, albeit "
"having a delicate frame that could be destroyed instantly by a well-placed "
"attack. However, a ‘well-placed attack’ would be difficult to place on these "
"elementals, given their highly resistant bodies of air.\n"
"\n"
"Still, summoners who stir such beings into their world know that an air "
"elemental could vanish just as quickly as it was summoned forth."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Air_God, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Air_God.cfg:4
msgid "Air God"
msgstr "大气之神"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Air_God, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Air_God.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Men fear the wind — what can be a gentle zephyr in the afternoon can turn "
"into a twister in the evening. Wind and storm can turn the staunchest man "
"into a rag doll dancing in the sky; lightning will then shoot him down back "
"to earth. Yet air gods have much more to be feared, for they ride upon their "
"own wind and bring about disasters at a mere order. Gods of the air are nigh "
"immune to physical assault with bodies that appear almost identical to an "
"actual storm.\n"
"\n"
"Summoners believe that even the heavens quake upon the sight of this great "
"nimbus of raging thunder and rain living in the skies, extending calamity to "
"wherever the eye of its storm gazes."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Air_God.cfg:122
msgid "storm"
msgstr "风暴"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Banisher, race=eoma_summoner
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Banisher.cfg:4
msgid "Banisher"
msgstr "放逐者"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Banisher, race=eoma_summoner
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Banisher.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Banishers represent the greatest level of skill a dispeller can achieve. "
"They can send to the Abyss magical beings that are too powerful for their "
"less experienced colleagues, much more powerful than those a fellow "
"Dispeller can. Like most experienced Summoners, Banishers march into battle "
"with magical circles, but ones using the dispelling magic. It is unclear how "
"or why circles of banishment work, but field scouts report multiple "
"sightings of magical entities tending to destabilize when close to them, "
"thus contributing to the Banishers' task."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=arcane
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Banisher.cfg:130
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dispeller.cfg:38
msgid "banishment"
msgstr "放逐"

#. [attack]: type=cold
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Banisher.cfg:152
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dispeller.cfg:60
msgid "frozen gate"
msgstr "冰冻之门"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Camel_Master, race=eoma_summoner
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Camel_Master.cfg:4
msgid "Camel Master"
msgstr "骆驼大师"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Camel_Master, race=eoma_summoner
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Camel_Master.cfg:19
msgid ""
"A Camel Master represents the pinnacle of excellence among camel riders, "
"boasting unparalleled prowess with deadly scimitars and lightning-fast "
"agility on their mounts. These masters hold the highest regard within their "
"respective communities and are frequently sought out to lead smaller "
"contingents of less experienced riders into battle. Their exceptional skills "
"and dedication have earned them the highest ranks within their societies, "
"and they are considered among the most formidable warriors in the land."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=blade
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Camel_Master.cfg:48
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Camel_Rider.cfg:46
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Elite_Camel_Rider.cfg:45
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Grand_Summoner.cfg:180
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Heavy_Summoner.cfg:218
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Neutral_Summoner.cfg:186
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Novice_Summoner.cfg:59
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Summoner.cfg:45
msgid "scimitar"
msgstr "弯刀"

#. [attack]: type=blade
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Camel_Master.cfg:57
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Camel_Rider.cfg:55
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Elite_Camel_Rider.cfg:54
msgid "scimitar throw"
msgstr "投掷弯刀"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Camel_Rider, race=eoma_summoner
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Camel_Rider.cfg:4
msgid "Camel Rider"
msgstr "骆驼骑手"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Camel_Rider, race=eoma_summoner
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Camel_Rider.cfg:19
msgid ""
"For the fledgling soldier, camels are a rare spectacle to be seen on the "
"fronts. Unlike their traditional brothers and sisters used as beasts of "
"burden for travelling traders, the camels seen in battle are specially bred "
"for speed and power rather than endurance. Riders carry a scimitar for melee "
"skirmishes as well as dozens of smaller scimitars to hurl at faraway "
"targets, a skill for which the camel rider is acclaimed for.\n"
"\n"
"Trained in scouting and hit-and-run warfare, camel riders are the "
"forerunners of the Summoners’ brunt strength, moving at galloping speed into "
"the fray."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Carpet_Master, race=eoma_summoner
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Carpet_Master.cfg:4
msgid "Carpet Master"
msgstr "飞毯大师"

#. [advancement]: id=damage_amla
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Carpet_Master.cfg:20
msgid "+2 magical powder damage; +3 max HP; +20% XP"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement]: id=veryskilled_amla
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Carpet_Master.cfg:47
msgid "Very Skilled instead of Marksman on magical powder; +2 max HP; +20% XP"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement]: id=hitandrun2_amla
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Carpet_Master.cfg:78
msgid "+Hit and Run 2; +2 max HP; +25% XP"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement]: id=melee_amla
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Carpet_Master.cfg:130
msgid "+1 strike and +skilled on irritant powder; +3 max HP; +20% XP"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Carpet_Master, race=eoma_summoner
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Carpet_Master.cfg:163
msgid ""
"Captains of the winds, any carpet master can attest to having ridden the "
"skies more times than he can count. A carpet master’s worth is still his "
"ability to scout over long distances, though his ranged attacks have become "
"something to be feared. Through battle, his accuracy with the powder bombs "
"has improved considerably, allowing him to strike even the most elusive or "
"well-protected of targets. Prized with a more regal carpet, the carpet "
"master soars through the air as effortlessly as any bird."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Carpet_Master.cfg:185
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Carpet_Rider.cfg:46
msgid "irritant powder"
msgstr "催泪粉尘"

#. [attack]: type=cold
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Carpet_Master.cfg:197
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Carpet_Rider.cfg:55
msgid "magical powder"
msgstr "魔法粉尘"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Carpet_Rider, race=eoma_summoner
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Carpet_Rider.cfg:4
msgid "Carpet Rider"
msgstr "飞毯骑手"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Carpet_Rider, race=eoma_summoner
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Carpet_Rider.cfg:21
msgid ""
"According to legend, the magic carpet originated from the desires of of a "
"wealthy princess. She wished for a new mode of traveling that would be "
"convenient and relaxing, yet ostentatious enough for her tastes. Carriages "
"and camels were too common and bland in her eyes, so she sought something "
"that would revolutionize transportation in the Summoners’ society. "
"Eventually, one of her expert sorcerers wove enchanted pieces of fabric "
"together to form what he called a ‘flying carpet’. Soon after, all affluent "
"men and women began riding these magic carpets for their personal "
"endeavors.\n"
"\n"
"Inevitably, magic carpets became of great importance in times of war, ridden "
"only by the most hotshot and fearless young men. Atop their strange mounts, "
"these aces of the sky perform impressive feats of reconnaissance and speed. "
"A magical carpet cannot hold much weight, so their riders are armed with "
"explosive powder bombs which they use to attack and disorient their targets."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_DharmaRhami, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dharma_rhami.cfg:4
msgid "Dharma’rhami"
msgstr "罗刹"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_DharmaRhami, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dharma_rhami.cfg:21
msgid ""
"With skin as red as blood, armed with more weapons than a human could hold, "
"and carrying a cup of raging fire, Dharma'rhami's appearance is likened to "
"that of a frenzied war god. While they are usually believed to be extremely "
"hot-tempered because of this, they are actually quite calm and judicious, "
"using their displays of power as an intimidation tactic and fighting with no "
"lust for bloodshed. Always keen to show off their remarkable skill with "
"their weaponry, they are said to be capable of crushing any opposition with "
"ease."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=blade
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dharma_rhami.cfg:61
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Rhami_datu.cfg:63
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Tharis\Sword_Dancer.cfg:176
msgid "swords"
msgstr "剑"

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#. [attack]: type=blade
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dharma_rhami.cfg:74
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Rhami_kai.cfg:57
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Rhami_kai.cfg:69
msgid "divine spear"
msgstr "神圣之矛"

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dharma_rhami.cfg:86
msgid "tackle"
msgstr "阻截"

#. [attack]: type=fire
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dharma_rhami.cfg:99
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Rhami_datu.cfg:76
msgid "cup of fire"
msgstr "火焰之杯"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Dimensional_Gate, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dimensional_Gate.cfg:15
msgid "Dimensional Gate"
msgstr "次元门"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Dimensional_Gate, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dimensional_Gate.cfg:29
msgid ""
"The most inexperienced of summoners are capable of summoning only "
"dimensional gates: unstable bridges of arcane energy between this world and "
"the Abyss. Dimensional gates, though primitive, are capable of surging forth "
"with accurate pinpoint attacks of arcane matter. Although weak and fragile, "
"a single fallen life is all that the gate requires in order to solidify "
"itself into a true door for a being from the Abyss to emerge out of."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Dimensional_Gate_II, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dimensional_Gate_2.cfg:15
msgid "Dimensional Gate II"
msgstr "次元门II"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Dimensional_Gate_II, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dimensional_Gate_2.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Dimensional Gate II is a more sophisticated variant of a typical blue gate. "
"It can be created only by summons experts or via the process of banishing a "
"more powerful magical being like Rhami'datu or Great Jinni. Summoners "
"consider Dimensional Gates II extremely valuable because of their improved "
"connection to the Abyss which allows summoning much more powerful beings in "
"exchange for a living or magical being's soul."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=arcane
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dimensional_Gate_2.cfg:234
msgid "yellow flame"
msgstr "黄焰"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Dispeller, race=eoma_summoner
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dispeller.cfg:4
msgid "Dispeller"
msgstr "驱散者"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Dispeller, race=eoma_summoner
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Dispeller.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Some summoners choose the opposite path of the summoning: the art of "
"banishment. Instead of bringing magical beings to this world, they "
"specialize in sending them back to Abyss. Normally such a skill would be "
"rather redundant, but due to the frequent Efreet rebellions, it is crucial "
"for upholding order in the summoner society."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Earth_Avatar, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Earth_Avatar.cfg:4
msgid "Earth Avatar"
msgstr "大地化身"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Earth_Avatar, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Earth_Avatar.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Avatars of the earth, though colossal, are slow-moving, hobbled by the "
"weight of their bulk. For this reason, earth avatars are bought out into the "
"battlefield for defending important landmarks such as mountains and "
"hilltops. Situated in defensible areas, avatars with their outlandish "
"strength crush parties of opposition while bracing against all varieties of "
"attacks. When all is done, these giants stand still and tall like massive "
"sculptures; over time, avatars begin to house tiny sprigs of vegetation "
"growing outside of its rocky cracks."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Earth_Avatar.cfg:64
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Earth_Elemental.cfg:74
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Earth_God.cfg:64
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Earth_God.cfg:76
msgid "hit"
msgstr "打"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Earth_Elemental, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Earth_Elemental.cfg:4
msgid "Earth Elemental"
msgstr "土元素"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Earth_Elemental, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Earth_Elemental.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The most unswerving of all elementals are the ones born from the earth. Such "
"large elementals carry the strength of easily ten men each, but their true "
"function are living fortresses, defending lines of troops with their "
"uncompromising and sturdy rock-skin. Earth elementals are capable of "
"withstanding barrages of blows before finally collapsing into shambles of "
"stones, returning back to the earth.\n"
"\n"
"After their summoning from the Abyss, earth elementals are imbued with "
"regenerative abilities by their summoners to improve them as living shields, "
"thus expanding their lifespans and their services to their masters."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Earth_God, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Earth_God.cfg:4
msgid "Earth God"
msgstr "大地之神"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Earth_God, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Earth_God.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Earth gods are simply gargantuan: one raised fist can shake the very "
"foundations of the land. Many tales have been told about the work of such "
"gods who lumber across the earth, so great in size that entire villages are "
"dwarfed by their presence. Bulwarks against the strongest swords, lances, "
"and spells, packing enough force to pulverize dozens in a single downward "
"strike, and continuously regenerating their stony bodies, earth gods are no "
"easy feat to bring down-or even force back."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Efreet, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Efreeti.cfg:4
msgid "Efreeti"
msgstr "火怪"

#. [unit_type]: id=EoMa_Efreet, race=eoma_magical
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Efreeti.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Cataclysmic by nature, efreets are jinn who have rejected most, if not all, "
"of their inner desires to learn. Efreets, for profound reasons beyond the "
"comprehension of their peers, search to cause destruction in their "
"conquests. To this, their magical bodies have sunken into a crimson-reddish "
"hue, tempering their magic with fire’s touch. In battles, efreets bask in "
"razing and laying waste to whatever their blazes can reach."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=fire
#. [attack]: type=arcane
#. [attack]: type=cold
#: Era_of_Magic\units\Summoners\Efreeti.cfg:78
